{
 "name": "RPlog_SW1_Log_2000-08-08-3",
 "title": "Recruiting Snarl and Zik",
 "summary": "In the plaza before the Coruscant palace, the Intelligence officer Bazil McKenzie meets the towering Horansi warrior Snal'Fashtalli, called Snarl, wife of the Sullustan Enb'Zik, after the pair were recently endangered in the underworld. The two converse with mutual respect about Bazil's violent line of work, his free-spirited distaste for protocol, and Snarl's dissatisfaction with the prejudice she faces as a non-human guard in the Caspar military. Snarl reveals she has all but cut herself off from her homeworld of Mutanda by marrying Zik, and confesses how the metal cityscape of Coruscant gives her claustrophobia. Touched by their plight, Bazil tells her of a mountain sanctuary to the south and then offers both her and Enb'Zik positions with his Intelligence branch -- freelance or staff, with freedom and compensation -- in the desperate fight against the rising Empire and its Death Star, an offer Snarl listens to with cautious interest.",
 "rows": [
